issue.title: Invalid "Annotate" button redirection

repository.name: doccano
repository.description: Open source annotation tool for machine learning practitioners.

issue.body:
<!-- Before submitting an issue, make sure to check the docs and closed issues and FAQ to see if any of the solutions work for you. https://github.com/chakki-works/doccano/wiki/Frequently-Asked-Questions -->

<!-- Include a code example or the steps that led to the problem. Please try to be as specific as possible. -->

<!-- Include details of your environment.-->

The "Annotate" button on an individual list item is supposed to open that particular record to annotate but it is opening any random record.

Observation: If the displaying list is of size 10, then it opens the 10th index and if the size is 100, then it opens the 100th index irrespective of your selected("clicked") sample.

How to reproduce the behaviour
---------
1. load more than 100 records 
2. goto dataset and change the list size from 10 to 100 
3. click on > to load different records on the list
4. click on "Annotate" 
5. it will open 100th record irrespective of chosen one.

Access Control should be ...

|             | -auth/-role | +auth/-role | +auth/+role | admin |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------|
| /projects/  | x           | o           | o           | o     |
| /project/x/ | x           | x           | o           | o     |

But now... (maybe)

|             | -auth/-role                 | +auth/-role | +auth/+role | admin |
|-------------|-----------------------------|-------------|-------------|-------|
| /projects/  | x (403 but no login (#518)) | x?           | **x**  (#574 )     | o     |
| /project/x/ | x                           | x           | o           | o     |

* auth: login authentication (-: can't login, +: can login)
* role: has role to the specific project (-: doesn't have role, +: has role)

issue.body:
**UPD: Not updating since 1.1.0 (26 January 2021).**

Good day!

Thank you for your GREAT work!

I have some enhancement requests... Just for a note, maybe. I will update them permanently.

1. ~URLs should become to a corresponding state. On Dataset page, URL is `/projects/4/dataset`. But refreshing the page redirects to `/projects/4` (#595; implemented in #897; see also #992, 976).~
2. ~Pagination, "rows per page" should change URL (#595; also mentioned in #540, #578; implemented in #897). And moreover: every view state should have its own URL.~
3. Put label hints and key shortcut hints back to Annotation page (#635 (merged in non-equivalent #834); mentioned in #509, #627, #776, #991, #1035; see also #829, #834).
4. Show number of imported rows (#1078).
5. Show number of deleting rows only in confirm dialog. It's difficult to delete many rows (#1077).
6. ~Add First/Last pagination links (#615; implemented in #981).~
7. ~IMHO menu should be opened on Project page and/or subpages by default (implementated in #598).~
8. Make limits configurable (#708, #1119, #1124; mentioned in #514 (merged to #521), #575, #706, #853, #1175).
